Haidut likes that "To Extract Knowledge from Matter" idea, where interacting with the living world's matter leads to you discovering more of its properties. Ray Peat quoted some Brazilian philosopher on how "naming the world" rearranges it as a question, necessitating a new name.

But the basic idea is the same. That you can always find something new, some new and deeper aspect of matter, bodies, tissues, life, etc. On a higher plane, I believe it is said God's science flows down to and through the Cherubim angels forever without end. Knowledge has no end.
